The '''FX-series medical assistant droid''',<ref name="SWCT" /> also referred to as a '''FX-series medical droid''',<ref name="Master of Evil">''[[Master of Evil]]''</ref> or as '''Fixits''', was a [[medical droid]] that was part of ten-model series manufactured by [[Medtech Industries]]. They were often paired with [[2-1B surgical droid|2-1B-series medical droid]]s.<ref name="SWCT" /> The FX-series had a similar name<ref name="A New Dawn (novel)" /> to the FX-2 droid<ref name="Cataclysm">''[[The High Republic: Cataclysm]]''</ref> and [[FX-6 droid]],<ref name="Silver Dawn">''[[The Vow of Silver Dawn]]''</ref> both of which had been seen in the [[High Republic Era]].<ref name="Cataclysm" /><ref name="Silver Dawn" />

They were designed with multiple arms and to look after patients, perform tests, operate equipment and recommend procedures.<ref name="SWCT" /> Two such [[droid]]s were [[FX-9 surgical assistant|FX-9]] and [[FX-7]];<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars" /> the former supplied the severely wounded [[Anakin Skywalker|Darth Vader]] with blood transfusion during his major surgery,<ref name="ROTS" /> and the latter monitored [[Luke Skywalker]] when he was recovering in a [[bacta tank]].<ref name="ESB" />

